@NODE INTRO "ProPassWord Documentation"

              @{U}AN INTRODUCTION TO PROPASSWORD, BY ANDREW GUARD@{UU}

Well hello, and welcome to ProPassWord (herein known as PPW).

If you have used ProPassWord before some of the ideas will come to you more
quickly. If you haven't used ProPassWord before you will benefit most from
this part of the guide.

First of all PPW is program which gives your system a FOF (Friend or Foe) 
gateway. This is done so that you can have more control over who uses your
system. PPW has some features which will be new to you at first but
everything will be clear soon.

If you use a naff OS at work which crashes every 5 minutes (guess which :)
some of this wouldn't sound new to you.  But their version of a Friend
Or Foe system in my opinion is naff (like everything else they release).  
Did you know that to get around their screen saver password system all you
have to do is have the CD installed and then remove it. Then the naff system
will ask you if you want to eject the CD.  Well there you are, you have now
bypassed the 'cool' security system.
 
I have some strange ideas about what a program like this should do. 
Some things I wish I could do are not permitted in AmigaOS 3.1.

Included in this package are two programs, ProPassWord, and
GenerateProPassword, let me explain what both of them do.

@{U}ProPassWord@{UU}

PPW is just a front end which asks the user for their PassWord and User 
Name. It also does other things which I will explain later on, explaining
it all now would just confuse you!.

There are NO back doors in PPW. There were version which had backdoors but
you would be informed of them if you run the program from CLI (Shell).
Only Beta testers should have these versions of the program. It is done just
as an escape system if the beta tester finds a bug. This version has NO
backdoors, all backdoors have been removed. That doesn't mean that there
isn't hidden messages in the program. The hidden messages will only be
display if a valid user name is entered.

@{U}GenerateProPassword@{UU}

GPPW is the main program, which confuses most people at first. This is 
because GPPW is where all user management takes place. You use GPPW to add 
new users, edit them or delete users. It also does lot more than this.

The reason that PPW and GPPW have been made as 2 seperate programs is for
security. Well you know that you remove that Format program from your
system if you want to make it harder to do Format, the same goes for GPPW.

                        @{" " LINK MAIN} - Back to Contents Page.
@ENDNODE

@NODE SYSREQ "ProPassWord Documentation"

                            @{U}SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS@{UU}

To run ProPassWord, you will need at LEAST the following system:

An Amiga equipped with a 68020 processor or above. Fast memory is
essential.

PPW now works with an AGA PAL/NTSC system, and even Amiga fitted with
graphics cards.

If you do not have such a system, it is still possible to use PPW, but it
is very risky. Simply supply @{FG HIGHLIGHT}FORCE@{FG TEXT} as a parameter to PPW when you run it.

                        @{" " LINK MAIN} - Back to Contents Page.
@ENDNODE

