@NODE INSTALL "ProPassWord Documentation"

                               @{U}INSTALLATION@{UU}

At the moment there is no installation script, so manual installation is
the only option. However, this is relatively easy. Just follow these simple
steps:

   1) First of all, delete the following files (if they exist):

      	S:Config_ProPassWord
      	ETC:PassWD.PPW

   2) Add the following line somewhere in your startup-sequence or
      user-startup file (they are stored in S:)

      	Assign ETC: <<Anywhere you like!>>

      Where <<Anywhere you like!>> is the COMPLETE path to, well, anywhere
      you like! For example, if I wanted ETC: to be assigned to the Temp
      directory on my Work: Partition, the line would look like:

			Assign ETC: Work:Temp/

      The ETC: assign is where the password list, and other files are
		stored.

   3) Copy the two program executables to C: These two are:

  			GenerateProPassword
         ProPassWord

   4) Add this line AFTER the line you added in Step 2:

         C:ProPassWord
  
   5) Installation complete! Copy the documentation wherever you like.

Now use GenerateProPassWord to configure your copy of the program. Then,
once you have done so, you are ready to use ProPassWord!

